[{"data":1,"prerenderedAt":330},["ShallowReactive",2],{"header-locale:\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2022\u002F05\u002F24\u002Fcomputer-screenshot-tutorial-windows-mac\u002F":3,"page:\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2022\u002F05\u002F24\u002Fcomputer-screenshot-tutorial-windows-mac\u002F":4,"alt:\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2022\u002F05\u002F24\u002Fcomputer-screenshot-tutorial-windows-mac\u002F":3,"prev-next:\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2022\u002F05\u002F24\u002Fcomputer-screenshot-tutorial-windows-mac\u002F":305,"related:\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2022\u002F05\u002F24\u002Fcomputer-screenshot-tutorial-windows-mac\u002F":314},"\u002Fother\u002F20220524\u002F3952721187\u002F",{"id":5,"title":6,"abbrlink":7,"altUrl":3,"body":8,"category":285,"date":286,"description":19,"extension":287,"lang":288,"meta":289,"navigation":290,"path":291,"readingMinutes":292,"seo":293,"standalone":294,"stem":295,"tags":296,"tldr":302,"updated":286,"url":303,"__hash__":304},"content\u002Fen\u002FMisc\u002Fcomputer-screenshot-tutorial-windows-mac.md","Don't Know How to Screenshot? Let Me Teach You — Windows and Mac in One Go","9527211873",{"type":9,"value":10,"toc":271},"minimark",[11,16,20,24,27,72,82,93,97,103,113,116,123,126,132,137,140,157,160,171,175,194,201,210,214,217,223,226,229,233,241,244,249,258,262,265],[12,13,15],"h2",{"id":14},"intro","Intro",[17,18,19],"p",{},"Screenshotting is something we use constantly, so here's a quick share of how to screenshot on Mac and Windows. And please — when possible, avoid using your phone to photograph the screen ~",[12,21,23],{"id":22},"macos-screenshots","macOS screenshots",[17,25,26],{},"Mac has built-in screenshot and screen recording. Just press the combo. Here are the combos:",[28,29,30,42,52,62],"ul",{},[31,32,33,37],"li",{},[34,35,36],"code",{},"Command + Shift + 3",[28,38,39],{},[31,40,41],{},"Capture the current full screen",[31,43,44,47],{},[34,45,46],{},"Command + Shift + 4",[28,48,49],{},[31,50,51],{},"Capture a portion of the screen",[31,53,54,57],{},[34,55,56],{},"Command + Shift + 5",[28,58,59],{},[31,60,61],{},"Screen recording \u002F capture toolbar",[31,63,64,67],{},[34,65,66],{},"Command + Shift + 6",[28,68,69],{},[31,70,71],{},"Capture the Touch Bar",[17,73,74,75,78,79,81],{},"I most often use \"",[76,77,51],"strong",{},"\" and \"",[76,80,61],{},"\". You should learn these two combos for sure.",[17,83,84,85,88,89,92],{},"Note: Mac's built-in screenshots are ",[34,86,87],{},".png"," and recordings are ",[34,90,91],{},".mov",". Filenames typically include the date and time.",[94,95,51],"h3",{"id":96},"capture-a-portion-of-the-screen",[17,98,99,100,102],{},"The simplest screenshot: press ",[34,101,46],{},". You get a selection cursor — select the area you want, and it auto-saves the file.",[17,104,105,106,108,109,112],{},"If you don't want to save but just copy the selection to clipboard, press ",[34,107,46],{},", then when the cursor appears, also hold ",[34,110,111],{},"Control"," (don't release) while selecting. That copies the image directly to clipboard (memory) without saving the file.",[17,114,115],{},"I know this is a bit tricky, so here's a GIF for reference:",[17,117,118],{},[119,120],"img",{"alt":121,"src":122},"Save to memory","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002Fother\u002F%E8%9E%A2%E5%B9%95%E9%8C%84%E8%A3%BD%202022-05-24%2009.40.33.gif",[94,124,61],{"id":125},"screen-recording-capture-toolbar",[17,127,128,129,131],{},"When you press ",[34,130,56],{}," (screen recording \u002F capture toolbar), you'll see this row:",[17,133,134],{},[119,135],{"alt":61,"src":136},"https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FigcZd4f.png",[17,138,139],{},"Left to right:",[28,141,142,145,148,151,154],{},[31,143,144],{},"Capture full screen",[31,146,147],{},"Capture window",[31,149,150],{},"Capture portion of screen",[31,152,153],{},"Record full screen",[31,155,156],{},"Record portion of screen",[17,158,159],{},"If you also want to record audio, tweak in the Options menu.",[17,161,162,163,170],{},"If you find Mac's built-in screenshot bad, you could install \"",[164,165,169],"a",{"href":166,"rel":167},"https:\u002F\u002Fapps.apple.com\u002Ftw\u002Fapp\u002Fskitch-%E9%80%9F%E6%8B%8D-%E6%A8%99%E8%A8%98-%E5%82%B3%E9%80%81\u002Fid425955336?mt=12",[168],"nofollow","Skitch","\".",[12,172,174],{"id":173},"microsoft-windows-screenshots","Microsoft Windows screenshots",[17,176,177,178,181,182,185,186,189,190,193],{},"Windows has built-in screenshot in every version — the ",[34,179,180],{},"Print Screen"," key (also labeled ",[34,183,184],{},"PrtScn"," or ",[34,187,188],{},"PrtScrn","). You can also use the built-in Snipping Tool, or ",[34,191,192],{},"[Windows key] + Shift + S"," for the capture tool.",[17,195,196,197,200],{},"Windows 10+ also has built-in screen recording — press ",[34,198,199],{},"[Windows key] + Shift + G"," to open it.",[17,202,203,204,209],{},"If you find the built-in bad, consider paid ",[164,205,208],{"href":206,"rel":207},"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.techsmith.com\u002Fscreen-capture.html",[168],"SnagIt"," (now also supports macOS).",[12,211,213],{"id":212},"lines-screenshot-tool","LINE's screenshot tool",[17,215,216],{},"If you don't want to install anything but still find built-in tools bad, I recommend LINE's screenshot tool. Open any chat window — the third button at the bottom is the screenshot tool:",[17,218,219],{},[119,220],{"alt":221,"src":222},"Screenshot tool","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002Fother\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202021-11-17%2017.36.30.png",[17,224,225],{},"Whichever screenshot method, it's way better than taking a photo with your phone — no screen reflection accidentally revealing your background or your dad-bod self.",[17,227,228],{},"So I'm serious: \"if you can use a screenshot tool, use a screenshot tool\".",[12,230,232],{"id":231},"vscode-code-snippet-screenshots","VSCode code snippet screenshots",[17,234,235,236,170],{},"A really handy trick — though it requires a plugin: \"",[164,237,240],{"href":238,"rel":239},"https:\u002F\u002Fmarketplace.visualstudio.com\u002Fitems?itemName=pnp.polacode",[168],"Polacode",[17,242,243],{},"Official demo below — you'll see why it's nice:",[17,245,246],{},[119,247],{"alt":240,"src":248},"https:\u002F\u002Fraw.githubusercontent.com\u002Foctref\u002Fpolacode\u002Fmaster\u002Fdemo\u002Fusage.gif",[17,250,251,252,257],{},"If you want to dig into more VSCode extensions, see my earlier post \"",[164,253,256],{"href":254,"rel":255},"https:\u002F\u002Fisraynotarray.com\u002Fvscode\u002F20191212\u002F2147775133\u002F",[168],"Essential VSCode Extensions for Developers","\" (article in Mandarin). It collects all the useful extensions I've used. Updated occasionally.",[12,259,261],{"id":260},"closing-thoughts","Closing thoughts",[17,263,264],{},"Lots of ways to screenshot — please just stop taking photos of your screen with your phone ~~",[17,266,267],{},[119,268],{"alt":269,"src":270},"GENIUS","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002Fother\u002FmessageImage_1636509060302.jpg",{"title":272,"searchDepth":273,"depth":273,"links":274},"",2,[275,276,281,282,283,284],{"id":14,"depth":273,"text":15},{"id":22,"depth":273,"text":23,"children":277},[278,280],{"id":96,"depth":279,"text":51},3,{"id":125,"depth":279,"text":61},{"id":173,"depth":273,"text":174},{"id":212,"depth":273,"text":213},{"id":231,"depth":273,"text":232},{"id":260,"depth":273,"text":261},"Misc","2022-05-24 09:06:39","md","en",{},true,"\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002Fcomputer-screenshot-tutorial-windows-mac","3",{"title":6,"description":19},false,"en\u002FMisc\u002Fcomputer-screenshot-tutorial-windows-mac",[297,298,299,300,301,240],"Mac Screenshot","Windows Screenshot","Windows 10 Screenshot","VSCode Screenshot","Computer Screenshot",null,"\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2022\u002F05\u002F24\u002Fcomputer-screenshot-tutorial-windows-mac\u002F","XiRz4fHap_fBDJgj-_i9TVwnaahJt1zA7KLgfH5isUg",{"newer":306,"older":310},{"url":307,"title":308,"date":309},"\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002F2022\u002F05\u002F25\u002Fgoogle-oauth2-with-express-and-passport\u002F","Google OAuth 2.0 with Express + Passport","2022-05-25 21:25:27",{"url":311,"title":312,"date":313},"\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002F2022\u002F05\u002F17\u002Fcomplete-express-imgur-upload-tutorial\u002F","The Complete Express + Imgur Upload Tutorial","2022-05-17 21:31:32",[315,320,325],{"url":316,"title":317,"date":318,"readingMinutes":319},"\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2026\u002F06\u002F23\u002Fmac-stats-menu-bar-system-monitor\u002F","Stats — The Free Open-Source macOS Menu Bar System Monitor I Use Every Day (CPU, GPU, Temperature, Network)","2026-06-23 10:00:00","5",{"url":321,"title":322,"date":323,"readingMinutes":324},"\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2026\u002F05\u002F26\u002Fhow-much-does-a-blog-really-earn-with-google-adsense\u002F","Can a Blog Really Make Tens of Thousands of Dollars a Month? Real Google AdSense Numbers, Explained","2026-05-26 21:00:00","6",{"url":326,"title":327,"date":328,"readingMinutes":329},"\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2026\u002F05\u002F18\u002Fvscode-disable-integrated-browser-auto-open\u002F","VSCode Opens Every Link in the Integrated Browser? How to Disable Auto Takeover","2026-05-18 14:30:00","4",1784020369819]